### WP Sign API Testing
### Sử dụng với REST Client extension trong VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@accessToken = 

### 1. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@acme.local",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### 2. Get Tenant Info
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 3. Upload Document
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fileName": "test-contract.pdf",
  "base64": ""
}

### 4. List Documents
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 5. Get Document Detail
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 6. Create Sign Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/sign-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "document_id": 1,
  "title": "Hợp đồng thuê nhà",
  "message": "Vui lòng xem và ký tài liệu này",
  "workflow_type": "sequential",
  "signers": [
    {
      "email": "signer1@example.com",
      "name": "Nguyễn Văn A",
      "role": "signer"
    },
    {
      "email": "signer2@example.com",
      "name": "Trần Thị B",
      "role": "approver"
    }
  ]
}

### 7. Get Sign Request
GET {{baseUrl}}/sign-requests/1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 8. Send OTP to Signer
POST {{baseUrl}}/signers/1/send-otp
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 9. Sign Document with OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/signers/1/sign
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otp": "123456",
  "signature_data": {
    "x": 100,
    "y": 200,
    "width": 150,
    "height": 50,
    "page": 1
  }
}

### 10. Cancel Sign Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/sign-requests/1/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 11. Get Audit Logs
GET {{baseUrl}}/audit/1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 12. Register Webhook
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/register
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://webhook.site/your-unique-url",
  "events": ["sign.completed", "document.uploaded"],
  "secret": "your-webhook-secret"
}

### 13. Delete Document
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/documents/1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 14. View Document (Open in browser) - Use Doc ID 1 or 2 (has real files)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/view
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 15. Download Document - Use Doc ID 1 or 2 (has real files)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/download
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### ========================================
### SECURITY: FILE PATH HARDENING

### 16. Test: file_path not exposed in list response
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
# Expected: Response should NOT contain file_path field
# Expected: Response should contain original_file_name field

### 17. Test: Path traversal attack (should be blocked)
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "file_name": "attack.pdf",
  "storage_path": "../../../etc/passwd",
  "document_type_id": 1
}
# Expected: 400 Bad Request with code INVALID_STORAGE_PATH

### 18. Test: Storage path outside base directory (should be blocked)
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "file_name": "attack.pdf",
  "storage_path": "/tmp/malicious.pdf",
  "document_type_id": 1
}
# Expected: 400 Bad Request with code INVALID_STORAGE_PATH

### ========================================
### DOCUMENT TYPES + NUMBERING INTEGRATION
### ========================================

### 14. List Document Types
GET {{baseUrl}}/document-types
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 15. Upload Document WITHOUT document_type_id (backward compatibility)
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "file_name": "test-no-type.pdf",
  "file_base64": ""
}

### 16. Upload Document WITH document_type_id (require_numbering = false)
# Expected: document_type_id set, document_number NULL
# Use document type ID from step 14 (e.g., "Hợp đồng" or type without numbering)
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "file_name": "contract-no-numbering.pdf",
  "file_base64": "",
  "document_type_id": 8
}

### 17. Upload Document WITH document_type_id (require_numbering = true, has rule)
# Expected: document_type_id set, document_number generated, numbering_rule_id set
# Use document type ID from step 14 (e.g., "Quyết định" ID=1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "file_name": "decision-with-numbering.pdf",
  "file_base64": "",
  "document_type_id": 1
}

### 18. Upload Document WITH document_type_id (require_numbering = true, NO rule)
# Expected: 400 error with code "NUMBERING_RULE_NOT_CONFIGURED"
# First, create a document type without numbering rule, or disable existing rule
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "file_name": "should-fail.pdf",
  "file_base64": "",
  "document_type_id": 999
}


### ========================================
### PHASE 1: DOCUMENT TAGS, PERMISSIONS, VERSIONS
### ========================================

### 1. Get All Tags (tenant-wide)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/tags/all
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 2. Add Tag to Document
# Replace :id with actual document ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tag": "urgent"
}

### 3. Add Another Tag
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tag": "confidential"
}

### 4. Get Document Tags
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 5. Remove Tag from Document
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tag": "urgent"
}

### ========================================
### DOCUMENT PERMISSIONS
### ========================================

### 6. Grant Permission to User
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject_type": "user",
  "subject_id": 1,
  "can_read": true,
  "can_edit": true,
  "can_approve": false,
  "can_share": true,
  "can_delete": false
}

### 7. Grant Permission to Department
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject_type": "department",
  "subject_id": 1,
  "can_read": true,
  "can_edit": false,
  "can_approve": true,
  "can_share": false,
  "can_delete": false
}

### 8. Get Document Permissions
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 9. Revoke Permission
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/permissions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject_type": "user",
  "subject_id": 1
}

### ========================================
### DOCUMENT VERSIONS
### ========================================

### 10. Create New Version
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/versions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "file_path": "/storage/documents/doc-v2.pdf",
  "change_summary": "Updated contract terms and conditions"
}

### 11. Create Another Version
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/versions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "file_path": "/storage/documents/doc-v3.pdf",
  "change_summary": "Fixed typos and formatting"
}

### 12. Get All Versions
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/versions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 13. Get Latest Version
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/1/versions/latest
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### ========================================
### COMBINED TEST: Upload Document with Tags
### ========================================

### 14. Upload Document
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "file_name": "test-document-with-tags.pdf",
  "file_base64": "",
  "document_type_id": 1,
  "title": "Test Document for Tags"
}

### 15. Add Multiple Tags to New Document
# Use document ID from previous response
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/2/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tag": "important"
}

### 16. Add Second Tag
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/2/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tag": "review-needed"
}

### 17. Verify Tags
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/2/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
